1
00:00:00,400 --> 00:00:05,550
Groundwater lagging is not just a signal delay.

2
00:00:05,550 --> 00:00:10,700
Lagging Theory focuses on flux-gradient asynchrony.

3
00:00:10,700 --> 00:00:16,900
Gradient and flux can evolve on different response paths.

4
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:26,050
Storage, drainage, leakage, pathways, exchange, and coupling can all create memory.

5
00:00:26,050 --> 00:00:32,450
A fitted curve can still transfer the wrong hydraulic parameter.

6
00:00:32,450 --> 00:00:40,700
The engineering test is whether memory changes pumping limits, recovery time, or risk.

7
00:00:40,700 --> 00:00:45,800
Lagging Theory turns groundwater memory into a decision test.
